PODGORICA, Montenegro â The Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS) has picked a successor to Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic, whose resignation was announced earlier this week. Meeting on Wednesday (October 4th), the DPS selected current Justice Minister Zeljko Sturanovic, 46. The choice must be approved by the party's board and then by parliament. Analysts expect smooth sailing, as the ruling coalition enjoys a strong parliamentary majority. (Pobjeda, Vijesti - 05/10/06; AP - 04/10/06)
